Dotfiles
========== 
This repository contains configuration files for my different systems. The
configurations can be cloned and installed according to the specific system in
use.


Systems
-------
common        : shared configuration files used across most systems
cloud         : self-hosted customised linux mint server
darwin        : macOS daily driver
devcontainer  : lightweight configs for devcontainers (does not use common/)
edge          : RaspberryPi edge server
wsl           : windows subsystem for linux environment


Archive
-------
The .archive/ directory contains configurations for tools I no longer
use. These are kept in case I revisit a previous tool or want to refer
back to details from an older setup.


Install
-------
The install.sh script installs all the required dependencies and creates the
necessary symlinks to set up the system. Clone the repository and run the script
specifying preferred configuration.

Alternatively, for a more detailed control and access to other cool stripts, use
my interactive shell script with the following command:

$ wget -qO- https://karsh.page/terminal | sh

